This annoys the most at the end of the game when you ride on a long bridge in the reverse direction.
The opponent must go ahead of you at all costs.
When he passes in front of you, he hides the sight of other vehicles in the reverse direction and you collide a good number of times.
One can understand that the goal of this game is to do something captivating and full of adredaline, but it is clear that you get bored quickly.
And it's a shame because through a simple driving model the game is interesting and places with so much action that you don't have time to follow everything that happens.
And it doesn't matter if it's because of the concept of 50 unique routes, that the order of the races is such that there's no chance of getting bored or something else.
The original idea is the change of car during the race.
You need to pay attention to gasoline pumps on the routes as you can change your car there however most of the time the one you have is enough for you.
The cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are ideal for cities, large U.S. cylinders for straight highways and super sports cars with exotic atours on highly technical pipes for example on lace roads in the mountains.
And the mode of challenges, which are races in particular places you know about adventure, goes very well with the main diet of history.
