When you reach the highest driver level, different objects begin to unlock themselves:
It connects online with the Autolog feature, which, among other things, compares your results with those of other players and provides you with other functions in the community.
One of the most difficult strokes to understand is the situation of the last race of the adventure.
You arrive with your car in the subway tunnel (it looks like) where you ride in the dark on the lanes (it looks like).
Your speed indicator tells you between 150 and 200 km/h (a priori) and behind you comes a subway railway that sends the car directly to the scrap.
At the writing we had a discussion for a few days as to whether someone really thought about creating this game or whether the authors really think of us as fools.
The technical part of the game is not extra,but the visual part is generally pleasant and in some cases really great.
What is annoying is that in more extreme situations, imaging does not hold the level and in some cases tragically.
This applies especially to accidents with a large number of participants when smooth imaging is no longer useful to you.
The sound part is good and the track is to choose from.
In order to please the greatest number and especially the most young audience a new soundtrack has been created in the "I mix everything" style, but one can expect that no one will buy the game for the music.
Need for Speed: The Run is really confused.
If the game didn’t have these stupid mistakes we could say without fear that it’s the best NFS production in recent years.
