In cases of arrests of more than 45 days, which were systematically controlled, 11% of cases were "inadequate or unjustified" out of 1.2 million, or 132,000.
In total, 169,000 "unjustified" cases out of several million employees who had a sick leave.
A figure that represents very little face to that of black work, for example.
